<br>
As far as opening the door goes, I have been on raids in HoT where someone would come in unannounced followed by drakes that would wipe us out.  This has happened more than once and I know has happened to other guilds.  The reason may not be the opening of the door, but it sure seemed that way.  Odd that the drakes rushing in was accompanied by people coming in those times.  It's not hard to see why people made the association.  I always thought it was a line of sight thing with the drakes. <p><p align="left"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26803"><img src="http://home.austin.rr.com/fianna/DoveSig.jpg" border="0"></a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uvorth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vorth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>TMS - GL</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/17/02 2:36:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=128.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.yopolis.com/syndicate/images/closeup_anim_text.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re</span><hr size=1> Bottom line is there is an infinte set of variables that interact with the door and agro on the hub npcs.  <br>
<br>
Faction Level of Player<br>
Player position<br>
Door Open or Closed<br>
Fighting a NPC<br>
NPC using AE<br>
Players using AE<br>
NPC Position<br>
Level of NPC being fought<br>
Level of NPC outside door<br>
<br>
Can the door open or close alone make the difference?  Probably not,  but there are at least 8 other conditions that can effect that.  <br>
