<br>
It's mighty strange how both the Door doesn't keep Area Effect from hitting the other side of it, AND keeps the drakes from agroing due to Area Effect at the same time.<br>
<br>
How can both of these scenarios be true?  Pull a red or white Ae'er to a pot and have people stand in the middle between the two pots getting hit by the AOE.  Have them stand all the way at the middle centerpiece so that they are not within natural agro range of the door.  Have someone stand around the corner out of AOE range, or someone outside open the door.  I bet ya money the Drakes come inside and whoop yer ass.  <br>
<br>
My hypothesis is that when the AOE hits the drake, the agro from the OTHER people being hit by same AOE is passed onto the drake somehow.  This may sound retarded, but it sure seems like whats going on from a logical standpoint.<br>
<br>
Being a Rogue, I will use something else as an example.  For the final epic hand-in, we have to turn a box into one of the dark elves in kithicor woods to spawn the general.  This mob we turn into is KoS to us, So we have to Sneak and turn it in from behind.  If there is an Undead creature within agro range when we come out of hide, we will still have enough time to turn our hand-in in before the dark elf attacks us, but the general will not spawn, and the dark elf will proceed to kill us.  What happened in this scenario was the Undead, which had not attacked us yet had passed his agro onto the dark elf, whom because he was agroed did not properly accept the item.<br>
<br>
It is very possible that the AOE hitting KoS people and a previouly un-KoS mob could pass agro onto the mob via the anger of the wurm you are fighting.  IF this holds any water whatsoever, it WAS opening the door, and allowing Line-of-Sight AOE damage to the Drake that caused the agro.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp,<br>
<br>
Jeshter Daggerfury<br>
