There are wanderers in the hub, who get much closer to the door than the two guards on the side. (have been kos to CoV for the past several months, memory is a bit shakey here.)  IIRC, there are 2 guards in the hub, facing towards the center.  There are about 4 mobs who wander, and get much closer to the door than anyone else does, and more importantly, when he's approaching the door, is facing it.  You can have a mob, as Rogg said, right up against the door when there's no wanderers nearby and you won't get aggro, independant of the door being open or closed. (the door being opened at this time probably <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> would</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> cause aggro because the mob would likely be bashed through it and much closer to the static spawn guards)  However, a wanderer will eventually walk up 20-30 seconds later, be facing the door (increasing aggro range dramatically) chain aggro everything, open the door, and kill everyone, resulting in the guildleader the door open is the cause rather than the effect.<br>
